    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Testudinella obscura. A – E. Loricae, ventral view. F. lorica, dorsal view. G. Lorica, caudal view. H. Foot pseudosegments. Scale bars: A – G: 50 µm, H: 25 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/187522/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.187523>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Testudinella obscura, scanning electron microscope photographs of trophi. A. Complete set, frontal view. B. Detail left manubrium. C. Complete set, caudal view. D. Complete set, lateral view. Scale bars: 10 µm. a: alula, dc: dorsal chamber, fo: fulcrum opening, mc: median chamber, sc: sub-ventral chamber, vc: ventral chamber." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/187523/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.187517>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Map indicating sampling areas and distribution of Testudinella bicorniculata sp. nov., T. elongata sp. nov. and T. obscura Althaus. S, Spain; F, France; E, Egypt; I, Italy; P, Philippines." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/187517/files/figure.png" ;
